{
  "doc_id": "22257",
  "text": "MiR-139 is consistently reported to be downregulated in several kinds of tumours, and involved in invasion and metastasis of colorectal cancer and hepatocellular carcinoma by targeting Rho-Kinase 2 [CITATION_1] and the type I IGF-IR [CITATION_2] respectively. Here, we preformed functional enrichment analysis on putative miR-139 targets and suggested that miR-139 most likely plays roles in cancer related functions, and oncogenic Jun might play central roles in these complicated miR-139-function networks. Experimental data confirmed that miR-139 inhibits Jun expression and affects gastric cancer via targeting Jun. So it's proposed here that miR-139 exerts tumour suppressive roles by coordinately targeting an array of related oncogenes including Jun.",
